Package CAMs_App.boundary

Class StudentMenu

java.lang.Object
CAMs_App.boundary.StudentMenu
All Implemented Interfaces:
Menu
public class StudentMenu extends Object implements Menu
The StudentMenu implements the generic menu, Menu. It provides methods to print the main menu and viewing the application. The class uses StudentController to manage student-related activities.

  • Method Details

    • printMenu

      public void printMenu()
      The printMenu() method displays the menu options available for student user. It prints student menu options such as view available camps, view registered camp(s), switch to camp committee mode, change password and logout.
      Specified by:
      printMenu in interface Menu

    • viewApp

      public void viewApp()
      The viewApp() method allows Student user to perform various actions such as

      • View available camps : Student user view the available camps by StudentController.viewAvailableCamp(). If a valid camp is entered in the list of available camps, the Student user will be navigated to StudentCampMenu or be prompted to switch mode to CampComMem if the selected camp is already registered as camp committee.
      • View registered camp(s) : Student user views the camp's that they have registered by StudentController.viewRegisteredCamp(). If the Student user registered a camp and selects a valid campname in the list, the Student user will be navigated to StudentCampMenu or be prompted to switch mode to CampComMem.
      • Switch to camp committe mode : Student user will switch into a camp committee mode CampComMem.
      • Changing password : Student user changes password via UserController.changePassword().
      • Logging out : Student user logs out from the system and returning to the MainMenu.

      Invalid inputs prompts the user to choose again.

      Specified by:
      viewApp in interface Menu
